  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are best dating apps/sites in india?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, several dating apps and sites have gained popularity in India, catering to a variety of preferences and demographics. Here are some of the best options:\n\n1. **Tinder**: A widely used app that allows users to swipe right to like or left to pass on profiles. It\u2019s popular among young adults and offers both casual and serious dating options.\n\n2. **Bumble**: Similar to Tinder, but with a twist\u2014women have to initiate the conversation after a match. This app empowers women and encourages more meaningful connections.\n\n3. **OkCupid**: Known for its detailed profiles and questionnaires, OkCupid helps users find matches based on compatibility and shared interests. It caters to various relationship types.\n\n4. **Happn**: This app connects users who have crossed paths in real life. It allows you to like or message people you\u2019ve encountered, making it a unique option for local connections.\n\n5. **Hinge**: Designed to be deleted, Hinge focuses on fostering long-term relationships. Users can engage with prompts on profiles, making conversations easier and encouraging deeper interactions.\n\n6. **TrulyMadly**: An Indian dating app that emphasizes safety and genuine connections. It uses a trust-based scoring system and various verification methods to ensure user authenticity.\n\n7. **Bharat Matrimony**: While primarily a matrimonial site, it caters to individuals looking for serious relationships and marriage. It is popular among people looking for traditional arrangements.\n\n8. **Shaadi.com**: Another matrimonial site focused on serious relationships, Shaadi.com is one of the largest platforms in India for people looking to get married.\n\n9. **Coffee Meets Bagel**: This app takes a quality-over-quantity approach by providing a limited number of matches daily. It encourages users to take their time to get to know each match.\n\n10. **Aisle**: A more curated dating platform that aims for serious relationships, Aisle focuses on bringing like-minded individuals together and discourages casual dating.\n\n11. **Woo**: Targeted primarily at Indian singles, Woo allows users to connect based on interests and preferences, with features like voice and video calls.\n\nWhen choosing a dating app, consider what kind of relationship you are looking for, as each platform has its unique focus and user base.",
